$ System.ConsoleColor (enum)

`System.ConsoleColor` is an enum that lists 16 predefined to color the background and characters of text in the console.
-
There are 8 base colors with a light and dark variant:
table { ll
  Black ☰ DarkGray
  Blue ☰ DarkBlue
  Cyan ☰ DarkCyan
  Green ☰ DarkGreen
  Magenta ☰ DarkMagenta
  Red ☰ DarkRed
  Yellow ☰ DarkYellow
  Gray ☰ DarkGray
table }

These colors correspond to the → Linux/shell/ANSI-escape-sequences#ansi-16-basic-colors[16 basic ANSI escape sequence colors].

sa:

  Powershell:
   • → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/automatic/host/privateData[`$host.privateData`]
   • → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/automatic/host/ui/rawUI/backgroundColor-foreground-Color[`backgroundColor` and `foregroundColor`] of the → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/automatic/host/ui/rawUI[`$host.ui.rawUI` object].
   • The various colors that can be set with → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/psReadLineOption/set[`set-psReadLineOption`]
